title: How have waiting times after an urgent referral changed by cancer type?
analysis_commentary: The proportion of people having an outpatient appointment within two weeks varied slightly by cancer type, but remained above 93.0% for all cancer types in all quarters. The highest rates were seen for testicular cancer, lung cancer and breast cancer. The lowest rates were seen for lower gastrointestinal cancer and upper gastrointestinal cancer.
